        "id": 1141499
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-03-04T22:33:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "must \u003e1, otherwise non-infra failures will also be retried. My understanding of quota algo in a nutshell:\n\nCQ attempt starts with quota counters:\n\n    per_builder \u003d collections.defaultdict(lambda: single_quota)\n    global \u003d global_quota\n\nthen when 1 builder fails:\n\n    per_builder[builder] -\u003d weight(failure_kind)\n    global_quota -\u003d weight(failure_kind)\n    if per_builder[builder] \u003e\u003d 0 and global_quota \u003e\u003d 0:\n      retry(builder)\n    else:\n      fail attempt",
      "parentUuid": "fdb865e9_97c13d99",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 119,
        "startChar": 23,
        "endLine": 119,
        "endChar": 24
      },
      "revId": "f44a2524d9838523f61f5b5e3aec7e8cda979408",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "69b8e23d_338f02a5",
        "filename": "lucicfg/starlark/stdlib/internal/luci/lib/cq.star",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 119,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-03-05T01:45:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Same question: why all existing configs use failure_weight \u003d 1? E.g. https://chromium.googlesource.com/chromium/src/+/refs/heads/master/infra/config/commit-queue.cfg#331\n\nI don\u0027t want to change it to avoid raising even more questions during the migration.",
      "parentUuid": "d6f97412_3a3669e0",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 119,
        "startChar": 23,
        "endLine": 119,
        "endChar": 24
      },
      "revId": "f44a2524d9838523f61f5b5e3aec7e8cda979408",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e68137a9_1a5c702e",
        "filename": "lucicfg/starlark/stdlib/internal/luci/lib/cq.star",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 119,
      "author": {
        "id": 1141499
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-03-05T01:56:56Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ah, this I can answer!\nBecause config was made for chromium only as CQ was only working for chromium at the time. And Chromium has flaky builders, so retrying non-infra failures was required.\n\nAs CQ acquired new users, the rest of projects didn\u0027t bother configuring this, and so inherited this.\nAnd I explicitly set this config during cq.cfg -\u003e commit-queue.cfg migration.\n\nThus, how about 3 constants?\nRETRY_2_FAILURES (1,2,1,1,2)\nRETRY_TRANSIENT_FAILURES (1,2,100,1,100)\nRETRY_NONE\n\nNote that for infra CQs, I\u0027ve actually removed retries to avoid letting flakes in, but I kept it for build repo for its PRESUBMIT is known to be flaky (master tests).",
      "parentUuid": "69b8e23d_338f02a5",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 119,
        "startChar": 23,
        "endLine": 119,
        "endChar": 24
      },
